3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates FET/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and mark price. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with Bybit taking no cut from the funding mechanism. Rates typically range from -0.01% to 0.375% per funding period, automatically debited or credited to positions based on the funding direction."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FET","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET represents Fetch.ai's growing AI agent ecosystem, making it susceptible to sentiment-driven funding rate volatility that creates arbitrage opportunities. The token's mid-tier trading volume on Bybit provides sufficient liquidity for meaningful position sizes while maintaining the volatility needed for profitable funding rate spreads."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown distinct patterns correlating with AI sector narratives and broader market sentiment. During AI hype cycles, positive funding rates frequently exceed 0.1% per 8-hour period as leveraged longs drive premium expansion. Conversely, during market downturns, negative funding rates of -0.05% to -0.1% create opportunities for long arbitrage positions. The pair exhibits higher funding rate volatility compared to major cryptocurrencies, with standard deviations typically 2-3x higher than BTC/USDT on the same exchange."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Implementation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Effective FET/USDT funding rate arbitrage on Bybit requires monitoring the 8-hour funding countdown and premium index movements. Long arbitrage positions benefit from negative funding rates while hedging with short spot or futures positions on other exchanges. Short arbitrage positions capture positive funding payments but require careful risk management due to FET's potential for sharp upward moves during AI sector rallies. Position sizing should account for Bybit's maintenance margin requirements and the token's inherent volatility, typically keeping leverage below 5x for sustainable arbitrage operations."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FET's AI sector classification introduces unique risks including narrative-driven price swings that can exceed funding rate profits within single 8-hour periods. Bybit's auto-deleveraging system may force position closures during extreme market moves, particularly problematic for FET given its occasional gap moves on AI-related news. Cross-exchange basis risk exists when hedging FET positions, as the token may experience different liquidity conditions across venues. Funding rate arbitrageurs should maintain stop-losses at 2-3x expected funding profits and monitor FET's correlation with broader AI tokens for early warning of sector rotation."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical FET/USDT funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"FET/USDT funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.1% to +0.2% per 8-hour period, with occasional spikes to ±0.375% during high volatility. The rates tend to be more volatile than major cryptocurrencies due to FET's AI sector positioning and mid-tier market cap."},{"question":"How does Bybit's 8-hour funding schedule affect FET arbitrage?","answer":"Bybit's 8-hour funding intervals at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to exchanges using 1-hour funding. This schedule often allows FET arbitrageurs to capture larger accumulated funding payments, particularly during sustained directional moves in AI token sentiment."},{"question":"What position size limits exist for FET/USDT on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit typically allows FET/USDT positions up to several hundred thousand dollars in notional value before encountering reduced leverage limits. The exchange's risk management system adjusts maximum leverage based on position size, often reducing from 25x to 10x or lower for positions exceeding $100,000 notional value."},{"question":"How does FET's AI sector correlation impact funding arbitrage?","answer":"FET's strong correlation with AI sector sentiment creates both opportunities and risks for funding arbitrage. During AI hype cycles, sustained positive funding rates can provide consistent arbitrage income, but rapid sector rotation can cause sudden funding rate reversals and underlying price gaps that exceed arbitrage profits."}]}]
